 <title>Piano Hero!</title>
 <link>http://hughsung.com/blog/index.php?itemid=1084?a=b</link>
<description><![CDATA[Who knew that playing the piano with the help of the <a href="http://airturn.com">AirTurn </a>could be more fun than playing video games?  Check out this wonderful "Piano Hero" video clip by Michael Monroe over at <a href="http://mmmusing.blogspot.com/2009/02/piano-hero-trailer.html">MMusing</a>!<br />
<br />
<object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/oc7UeLzndbM&hl=en&fs=1"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/oc7UeLzndbM&hl=en&fs=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="425" height="344"></embed></object><br />
<br />
Michael uses an extra monitor attached to his Tablet PC's VGA-out port to enable the 2nd pianist to see the score comfortably.  What a clever solution!  Certainly cheaper than the screen real estate from a $3000 17 in. MacBook Pro that i'm insanely mulling over...<br />
]]>

